author: Preeti Cholleti
text: Using AI to democratize and make data science accessible. hashtag#DataScienceInnovationFollow us on Discord: https://lnkd.in/gt823Zd3..Summary: The ChatGPT Code Interpreter is an extension of ChatGPT that allows users to solve math and data challenges using conversational language. It addresses the challenges of data science, such as skill shortages and steep learning curves, by empowering non-experts and automating data preparation. Data science is essential for extracting insights from datasets, propelling business growth, and improving various industries. However, data science also presents challenges like a shortage of data scientists, lack of advanced skills, high learning curves, and tedious data preparation. The Code Interpreter overcomes these challenges by providing an effortless and user-friendly solution for data analysis and manipulation. However, it also has its own limitations, such as database accessibility, internet access, limited file size, and lack of up-to-date data. Hashtags: hashtag#chatGPT hashtag#DataScienceRevolution hashtag#AIforAll

author: Matheus Davin Giovanni
text: ğŸŒ Quantum Computing: The Next Big Leap in Data Science? ğŸŒIn the realm of data science, quantum computing is emerging as a game-changer. Imagine being able to solve complex calculations that would take traditional computers yearsâ€”or even centuriesâ€”to complete. This is exactly what quantum computing promises, and its potential impact on data science is profound. ğŸš€ğŸ” Why Quantum Computing Matters in Data Science Quantum computing harnesses the power of quantum mechanics, allowing it to perform multiple calculations simultaneously. For data scientists, this means handling vast datasets, performing advanced analytics, and solving optimization problems at speeds unimaginable with current technology. Whether in cryptography, supply chain optimization, or machine learning, quantum computing could break barriers we previously thought insurmountable.ğŸ” Applications and Future Impact Quantum technology holds particular promise for fields like cryptography, where it could redefine secure data storage and communication. Itâ€™s also a game-changer in optimization problemsâ€”for instance, improving route planning, resource allocation, and even genetic algorithms used in medical research. But while the possibilities are exciting, quantum computing is still in its infancy. Researchers are tackling significant technical and cost-related challenges, but advancements are happening fast.ğŸŒ± The Journey Ahead Although weâ€™re in the early stages, organizations are already investing heavily in quantum research, anticipating a future where itâ€™s an integral part of the data science toolkit. author: Technovation
text: What is the role of human systems in data science innovations? ğŸ¤”New study in Technovation!!! ğŸ‘By: Keyao (Eden) Li, Mark Griffin Research Highlightsâ€¢ Human systems are critical, yet often neglected in most guidelines and frameworks for data science. We address this concern by developing a systematic framework for understanding human systems that support data science innovations.â€¢ A review of human system elements indicates that successful innovation requires supports at different levels of organisations, which combine to create the organisationâ€™s innovation capability.â€¢ Drawing on a series of interviews with key innovators engaged in developing current data science innovations, a more complete picture of human systems in practice was developed.â€¢ This study contributes to the advancement of innovation management theories and calls attention to guiding and engaging individuals through providing support and removing barriers at different organisational levels.â€¢ More practically, innovation managers could use this as a guide to optimise work systems and inform pathways to improve organisation data science efforts.Read the full article ğŸ‘‡https://lnkd.in/dkP6zW7phashtag#DataScienceInnovation hashtag#HumanSystems hashtag#InnovationManagement hashtag#DataScientist

author: Shekhar Singh Tomar
text: Data Science Myths and MisconceptionsData science is a rapidly growing field, and with it comes a lot of myths and misconceptions. These myths can prevent people from pursuing a career in data science, or from using data science to its full potential.Here are some of the most common data science myths and misconceptions:1. Data science is only for math geniuses.This is not true! Data science is a multidisciplinary field that requires a variety of skills, including math, statistics, programming, and communication. While a strong understanding of math is helpful, it is not essential for a successful career in data science.2. Data science is all about coding.While coding is an important skill for data scientists, it is not the only skill required. Data scientists also need to be able to understand and interpret data, communicate their findings effectively, and solve complex problems.3. Data science is only for big tech companies.Data science is used in a variety of industries, including healthcare, finance, retail, and manufacturing. Data scientists are in high demand across all industries, so there are many opportunities for data scientists to work in companies of all sizes.4. Data science is a job for introverts.Data scientists need to be able to communicate their findings to a variety of audiences, including technical and non-technical audiences. Data scientists also need to be able to collaborate with other team members to solve complex problems.5. Data science is a boring job.Data science is a very dynamic and challenging field. Data scientists are constantly learning new things and working on new problems. Data science is also a very creative field, and data scientists have the opportunity to use their skills to make a positive impact on the world.Here Some Pointers a) Data science is a multidisciplinary field that requires a variety of skills, including math, statistics, programming, and communication.b) Coding is an important skill for data scientists, but it is not the only skill required.c) Data science is used in a variety of industries, including healthcare, finance, retail, and manufacturing.d) Data scientists need to be able to communicate their findings to a variety of audiences and collaborate with other team members.e) Data science is a very dynamic and challenging field that offers many opportunities to learn and grow.Conclusion:Data science is a rapidly growing field with many exciting opportunities. If you are interested in a career in data science, don't let these myths and misconceptions hold you back. There are many resources available to help you learn the skills you need to be successful in data science.hashtag#datascientist hashtag#machinelearning hashtag#artificialintelligence hashtag#bigdata hashtag#dataanalytics hashtag#datavisualization hashtag#datasciencemyths hashtag#datasciencemisconceptions hashtag#datasciencelife hashtag#datascientistsoflinkedin hashtag#datasciencecommunity hashtag#datasciencetrends hashtag#datascienceinnovation

author: Amit Subhash Chejara
text: ğŸ¥ Understanding the Central Limit Theorem Through Simulation ğŸ“ŠThe Central Limit Theorem (CLT) is a fundamental concept in statistics, and Iâ€™ve used a quick simulation to demonstrate it in action!ğŸ” In the video, I start by taking a random distribution (which doesnâ€™t have to be normal). From this distribution, I repeatedly take 5 samples and calculate the mean of each sample. After doing this 10,000 times, you'll notice something fascinating:As I plot the sample means, the shape of the distribution starts looking more and more like a normal distribution (bell curve) ğŸ“ˆ.âœ¨ Whatâ€™s happening? The CLT states that no matter the shape of the original population distribution, the distribution of the sample means will tend to become normal if you take enough samples.This is a key principle that helps in data analysis, making the assumption of normality valid in many real-world applications! ğŸŒhashtag#FederatedLearninghashtag#AIInnovationhashtag#MachineLearningModelshashtag#AIRevolutionhashtag#TechForGoodhashtag#DecentralizedAIhashtag#DataDrivenhashtag#ArtificialIntelligencehashtag#TechUpdateshashtag#AIResearchhashtag#NextGenTechhashtag#GlobalAIhashtag#AICommunityhashtag#FutureOfAIhashtag#MachineLearningTechhashtag#TechSpecialisthashtag#DataScienceInnovationhashtag#AIforEveryonehashtag#DigitalTransformationhashtag#TechLeaders

author: Puneet Ananth Hegde
text: ğŸš€ Precision Engineering in Data Science: Transformative Insights from CIFAR-10 Dataset Analysis ğŸš€Dear LinkedIn community,I am thrilled to share a groundbreaking project, "Unraveling Data Science Precision: Insights from CIFAR-10 Dataset," that not only showcases the power of deep learning but also highlights our dedication to precision engineering in the dynamic world of data science.ğŸ” Decoding the Data Science Landscape:In the era where data drives innovation, our team embarked on a transformative journey, seeking to unravel the complexities of the CIFAR-10 dataset. Leveraging cutting-edge convolutional neural networks (CNNs), we optimized hyperparameters with meticulous precision and sculpted data into actionable insights.ğŸ’¡ Key Findings:Optimized Model Architecture: Our model, meticulously fine-tuned for nuanced pattern recognition, mirrors the intricacies of real-world data, a testament to our commitment to precision engineering.Hyperparameter Mastery: In the pursuit of precision, we selected the SGD optimizer with a learning rate of 0.001, a configuration proven effective in real-world data challenges.Batch Size Brilliance: Striking the perfect balance with a batch size of 32, we ensured efficiency without compromising accuracy, a vital consideration for large-scale data processing.Robust Regularization: Integration of Dropout and L2 regularization techniques fortified our model against overfitting, ensuring robust performance in complex data landscapes.ğŸŒŸ Implications and Conclusions:My findings have far-reaching implications. The precision engineering techniques we employed not only enhanced model performance but also emphasized the importance of meticulous calibration in the data science landscape. The synergy of hyperparameter optimization and regularization techniques resulted in a substantial test accuracy of 79.72%, showcasing our commitment to delivering actionable insights.This achievement is not just a milestone; it's an invitation to industry recruiters and developers to join us in revolutionizing data science. For recruiters seeking passionate data scientists and developers hungry for impactful projects, our journey signifies a dedication to excellence and an opportunity to redefine the boundaries of data science.hashtag#DataScienceInnovation hashtag#PrecisionEngineering hashtag#DataDrivenDecisions hashtag#TechInnovation hashtag#OptimizedAlgorithms hashtag#DataScienceResults hashtag#InnovateWithData hashtag#machinelearning hashtag#CIFAR10 hashtag#machinelearningengineer hashtag#deeplearningengineer hashtag#imageclassificationThank you for your time, and I look forward to connecting with like-minded professionals and developers. author: Rishabh Malwade
text: ğŸŒŸ Excited to share insights on the powerful Pareto Principle, also known as the 80/20 rule! ğŸš€ğŸ” The Pareto Principle states that roughly 80% of results come from 20% of efforts or causes. Here are 10 examples illustrating this principle:1ï¸âƒ£ In business, 80% of profits often come from 20% of customers.2ï¸âƒ£ In software development, 80% of errors are caused by 20% of bugs.3ï¸âƒ£ In sales, 80% of revenue is generated by 20% of the sales team.4ï¸âƒ£ In time management, 80% of productivity stems from 20% of tasks.5ï¸âƒ£ In sports, 80% of victories may result from 20% of training techniques.6ï¸âƒ£ In marketing, 80% of engagement comes from 20% of content.7ï¸âƒ£ In healthcare, 80% of patient complaints may relate to 20% of medical conditions.8ï¸âƒ£ In education, 80% of learning often occurs through 20% of course material.9ï¸âƒ£ In investing, 80% of returns can come from 20% of investment decisions.ğŸ”Ÿ In networking, 80% of opportunities may arise from 20% of connections.Understanding and leveraging the Pareto Principle can lead to more efficient allocation of resources and improved decision-making. author: Shahid ch.

author: Ali Abedini
text: ğŸš€ The Next AI Revolution? Itâ€™s Here!I recently dove into an incredible paper on CARTE and tabular foundation models, and itâ€™s inspiring to think about the future possibilities. Imagine a model for tabular data (spreadsheets, structured data) thatâ€™s as adaptable and powerful as ChatGPTâ€”CARTE is pushing us closer to this reality!Our own TD Layer 6 AI also expanded on this concept. One major challenge in tabular data is enabling neural networks to adapt quickly to new datasets without retraining. By leveraging in-context learning (ICL), our Tabular Discriminative Pre-trained Transformer (TabDPT) is designed to provide rapid, accurate predictions on new data without task-specific fine-tuning. This opens doors to faster, more versatile solutions in handling structured data, with state-of-the-art results on both classification and regression benchmarks. Check this out here: https://lnkd.in/gWdeiz39These models have the potential to replace traditional approaches like XGBoost with something smarter and more flexible, bringing faster insights across industries like finance, healthcare, and beyond. The idea of a model that learns and generalizes with minimal adjustment could be transformative, opening up entirely new ways of understanding data.Exploring these ideas got me excited about the possibilities. Who else sees a â€œChatGPT momentâ€ on the horizon for tabular data?hashtag#AIRevolution hashtag#DataScienceInnovation hashtag#TabDPT hashtag#TabularDataModels hashtag#MachineLearning hashtag#NextGenAI hashtag#AIForData hashtag#CARTE hashtag#TabularFoundationModels hashtag#FutureOfDataScience hashtag#XGBoostReplacement hashtag#DataScienceCommunity hashtag#AIInnovation

author: Dr. Vijay Varadi PhD
text: The article discusses common mistakes made in the field of data science and analytics, emphasizing the importance of integrating common sense, subject matter expertise, and ethical considerations into data analysis. It highlights the pitfalls of overreliance on advanced technologies like AI and ML without proper understanding of the problem, neglecting basic statistical principles, and providing solutions without addressing root causes. The article also addresses issues such as bias in funded research, the challenges of data sharing within organizations, and the dangers of presenting unfounded or biased analytical results. It stresses the necessity of embracing negative outcomes for their instructive value and maintaining integrity and transparency to ensure that analyses serve the true interests of businesses and their stakeholders. The piece concludes by underscoring the responsibility of data scientists to deliver unbiased, evidence-based insights that support ethical and effective business decisions, advocating for a commitment to rigorous, principled data science practice.hashtag#DataScienceEthics, hashtag#AnalyticalIntegrity, hashtag#BiasInAnalytics, hashtag#StatisticalPrinciples, hashtag#AIEthics, author: Abdullah K.
text: ğŸ” Exciting advancements in quantum computing! The recent paper on "Bayesian Parameter Shift Rule in Variational Quantum Eigensolvers" introduces a Bayesian variant of parameter shift rules (PSRs) for efficient gradient estimation in VQEs. By leveraging Gaussian processes, this approach offers flexible gradient estimation with uncertainty information, enhancing the optimization process. Key highlights include:- Reuse of observations in stochastic gradient descent (SGD) for accelerated optimization.- Introduction of the Gradient Confident Region (GradCoRe) to minimize observation costs.- Significant performance improvements over state-of-the-art methods.This breakthrough could pave the way for more efficient quantum computations! ğŸŒŸhashtag#AI hashtag#Algorithms hashtag#ArtificialIntelligence hashtag#BayesianPSR hashtag#DL hashtag#DS hashtag#DataScience hashtag#DataScienceInnovation hashtag#DeepLearning hashtag#GradientEstimation hashtag#ML hashtag#MachineLearning hashtag#QuantumComputing hashtag#Tech hashtag#Technology

Traditional AI platforms are often bound by the limitations of centralized infrastructure, facing challenges in scalability, security, and data interoperability. HoloStream pattern presents a new frontier for decentralized AI and data science by leveraging multichain connectivity and blockchain-backed infrastructure.HoloStream isnâ€™t just a decentralized data platform; itâ€™s a launchpad for collaborative, scalable, and privacy-preserving AI and data science. This article will outline how HoloStream can empower data scientists, ML engineers, and blockchain enthusiasts to create innovative solutions, and weâ€™ll introduce a series of upcoming hands-on labs that will showcase these possibilities in action.1Â Â Â Â Â Â Â HoloStream and the Future of Decentralized AI & Data ScienceAs data demands grow and decentralized technologies become more prevalent, the limitations of centralized AI and data science platforms are increasingly evident. Traditional platforms often rely on centralized infrastructure, which introduces bottlenecks in scalability, data privacy, and interoperability. These platforms also struggle to fully leverage multichain ecosystems, limiting their ability to handle data from Web3 applications and blockchain sources.HoloStream addresses these challenges with a groundbreaking approach. Designed with a decentralized architecture and multichain connectivity at its core, HoloStream allows data scientists and engineers to manage and process data across multiple blockchains and decentralized networks. By abstracting data storage, compute, and streaming layers, HoloStream enables end-to-end data science workflows to run on a blockchain-enabled infrastructure, breaking free from the centralized constraints of traditional AI platforms.See full article (attached)hashtag#DecentralizedAI, hashtag#DataScience, hashtag#Blockchain, hashtag#MachineLearning, hashtag#HoloStream, hashtag#FederatedLearning, hashtag#Web3, hashtag#DeFi, hashtag#DataScienceInnovation, hashtag#MultichainInnovation, hashtag#ZeroKnowledgeProofs, hashtag#ZKP, hashtag#MultichainAI, hashtag#DataMarketplace

author: Ivan L.
text: Unveiling the AI Revolution in Travel: Transforming Journeys with Data Science ğŸŒğŸ”While tech is not new to the travel industry, the travel industry is undergoing a seismic shift, thanks to data science and AI. Here are nine groundbreaking ways these technologies are making a difference:1) Personalized Recommendations: AI crafts unique travel suggestions, tailoring experiences to individual preferences.2) Dynamic Pricing: Advanced algorithms adjust prices for airlines and hotels in real-time, optimizing for market demand.3) Fraud Detection: AI enhances security in online bookings, safeguarding both companies and customers.4) AI-Powered Chatbots: These digital assistants provide instant, efficient customer service.5) Predictive Maintenance in Airlines: AI predicts maintenance needs, reducing delays and enhancing safety.6) Route Optimization: AI finds the most efficient routes, saving time and fuel.7) Demand Forecasting: AI anticipates travel demand, allowing airlines to adjust capacity proactively.8) Sentiment Analysis for Feedback: AI analyzes customer feedback, offering insights into service improvement.9) Image Recognition for Hotels: This technology classifies hotel rooms, enhancing the booking experience.By embracing these AI and data science applications, travel companies are not just improving customer experiences; they're revolutionizing them. They're optimizing operations, increasing revenue, and cutting costs, proving that when it comes to travel, the future is here and now.hashtag#TravelTech hashtag#AIInTravel hashtag#DataScienceInnovation

author: Tracy Bert
text: ğˆğ¬ ğ‚ğšğ®ğ¬ğšğ¥ ğ€ğˆ ğ­ğ¡ğ ğŠğğ² ğ­ğ¨ ğ”ğ§ğğğ«ğ¬ğ­ğšğ§ğğ¢ğ§ğ  ğ‚ğ¨ğ¦ğ©ğ¥ğğ± ğˆğ§ğ­ğğ«ğšğœğ­ğ¢ğ¨ğ§ğ¬ ğ¢ğ§ ğƒğ²ğ§ğšğ¦ğ¢ğœ ğ’ğ²ğ¬ğ­ğğ¦ğ¬? | Global Insight Servicesğƒğ¨ğ°ğ§ğ¥ğ¨ğšğ ğğƒğ… ğ’ğšğ¦ğ©ğ¥ğ ğ‘ğğ©ğ¨ğ«ğ­ : https://lnkd.in/dbh2gFftCausal AI, at its core, harnesses advanced machine learning algorithms and statistical methods to identify and understand causal relationships within complex systems. Unlike traditional AI approaches focused solely on correlations, Causal AI aims to uncover the underlying mechanisms driving observed phenomena. This involves not only predicting outcomes but also elucidating how one variable influences another directly or indirectly. By employing techniques such as causal inference and counterfactual analysis, Causal AI can discern cause-and-effect relationships from observational or experimental data. This nuanced understanding empowers businesses and researchers to make more informed decisions, optimize processes, mitigate risks, and even discover new opportunities previously obscured by purely correlational analyses. As Causal AI continues to evolve, its application spans diverse domains, from healthcare and finance to marketing and beyond, shaping the future of data-driven decision-making.hashtag#causalai hashtag#aiinanalytics hashtag#predictivecausality hashtag#causalinference hashtag#machinelearningtrends hashtag#causaldiscovery hashtag#datascienceinnovation hashtag#causalmodeling hashtag#algorithmiccausality hashtag#causalreasoning hashtag#counterfactualanalysis hashtag#aiindecisionmaking hashtag#causalunderstanding hashtag#causalityrevolution hashtag#aiforcausation

text: ğˆğ¬ ğ‚ğšğ®ğ¬ğšğ¥ ğ€ğˆ ğ­ğ¡ğ ğŠğğ² ğ­ğ¨ ğ”ğ§ğğğ«ğ¬ğ­ğšğ§ğğ¢ğ§ğ  ğ‚ğ¨ğ¦ğ©ğ¥ğğ± ğˆğ§ğ­ğğ«ğšğœğ­ğ¢ğ¨ğ§ğ¬ ğ¢ğ§ ğƒğ²ğ§ğšğ¦ğ¢ğœ ğ’ğ²ğ¬ğ­ğğ¦ğ¬? | Global Insight Servicesğƒğ¨ğ°ğ§ğ¥ğ¨ğšğ ğğƒğ… ğ’ğšğ¦ğ©ğ¥ğ ğ‘ğğ©ğ¨ğ«ğ­ : https://lnkd.in/dbh2gFftCausal AI, at its core, harnesses advanced machine learning algorithms and statistical methods to identify and understand causal relationships within complex systems. Unlike traditional AI approaches focused solely on correlations, Causal AI aims to uncover the underlying mechanisms driving observed phenomena. This involves not only predicting outcomes but also elucidating how one variable influences another directly or indirectly. By employing techniques such as causal inference and counterfactual analysis, Causal AI can discern cause-and-effect relationships from observational or experimental data. This nuanced understanding empowers businesses and researchers to make more informed decisions, optimize processes, mitigate risks, and even discover new opportunities previously obscured by purely correlational analyses. As Causal AI continues to evolve, its application spans diverse domains, from healthcare and finance to marketing and beyond, shaping the future of data-driven decision-making.hashtag#causalai hashtag#aiinanalytics hashtag#predictivecausality hashtag#causalinference hashtag#machinelearningtrends hashtag#causaldiscovery hashtag#datascienceinnovation hashtag#causalmodeling hashtag#algorithmiccausality hashtag#causalreasoning hashtag#counterfactualanalysis hashtag#aiindecisionmaking hashtag#causalunderstanding hashtag#causalityrevolution hashtag#aiforcausation

author: Robert McMenemy ğŸ‘¾
text: ğŸš€ Unleashing Predictive Power: Fibonacci Neural Networks Meet XGBoost Stacking ğŸŒŸAs the field of machine learning continues to evolve, innovative approaches are constantly emerging to push the boundaries of predictive performance. I'm excited to share a new article that dives into a powerful technique: stacking a Fibonacci-inspired neural network with XGBoost. This hybrid model leverages the strengths of both deep learning and gradient boosting to tackle complex classification tasks with remarkable accuracy and robustness.ğŸ” Why Fibonacci Neural Networks?Inspired by the Fibonacci sequence, this neural network architecture employs a series of layers that grow in size, capturing intricate patterns and relationships in the data. By integrating dropout and batch normalization, we ensure stability and prevent overfitting, making it a solid foundation for feature extraction.ğŸ”¥ The Power of XGBoost StackingXGBoost is renowned for its performance on structured data, and when combined with features extracted by the neural network, it delivers a formidable boost in prediction quality. Using a clever combination of early stopping and a validation set, we ensure that our model is optimized without overfitting, achieving outstanding results on the Breast Cancer Wisconsin dataset.ğŸ”— Check out the full article on Medium for a deep dive into the methodology and implementation detailsWhether you're a data scientist looking to improve your model's performance or simply curious about cutting-edge techniques in machine learning, this article offers valuable insights and practical guidance.hashtag#MachineLearning hashtag#DataScience hashtag#NeuralNetworks hashtag#XGBoost hashtag#AIInnovation hashtag#PredictiveAnalytics hashtag#DataScienceInnovation
